-- Mexicana Says Med Atlantica Is New Owner of Holding Company
-- B y   C a r l o s   M a n u e l   R o d r i g u e z
-- 2012-05-11T19:55:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-11/mexicana-says-med-atlantica-is-new-owner-of-holding-company-1-.html
Cia. Mexicana de Aviacion, the
airline that filed for bankruptcy protection in 2010, said Med
Atlantica is the new owner of its holding company’s shares, in
an e-mailed statement today.  Mexicana was  Mexico ’s largest airline by passengers when it
grounded flights in August 2010 and filed for bankruptcy
protection days later with total liabilities of 17 billion pesos
($1.3 billion).  To contact the reporter on this story:  Carlos M. Rodriguez in Mexico City at 
 carlosmr@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at   dcrofts@bloomberg.net  